article.headline: Penn 90, Illinois-Chicago 78
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Mark Zoller had 21 points and 13 rebounds, and Brian Grandieri scored 17 of his 19 points in the second half, leading Penn to a 90-78 victory over Illinois-Chicago on Thursday night. Steve Danley added 19 points for the Quakers (6-4), while Ibrahim Jaaber had six steals, raising his career total to 248, the most ever by an Ivy League player. Jaaber surpassed the record of 242, held by Andrew Gellert of Harvard (1998-2001). Othyus Jeffers had a career-high 27 points and 14 rebounds for UIC (6-7), and Jovan Stefanov added 12 points. After Jeffers completed a three-point play, the Flames led 58-53 with 15:39 left. The Quakers went on a 15-3 run to take a 68-61 lead. Grandieri scored nine points in the outburst. UIC closed within 70-66 with 7:39 to go, but Zoller hit a 3-pointer that sparked a 9-3 run and the Flames never got closer than eight points the rest of the way.
